<br>
 I knew their damage was already way off the chart and absolutely ridiculous, but seeing the pets as the preferred tank in an uber mob fight was the last straw.  High level charms are absurd now.  They've made things far more imbalanced than anything else I've ever seen in EQ.  Especially in an outdoor zone and especially if you have someone to snare the pet before it's charmed, the risk is low.  The raid party we were watching failed, but they proved that the pet tanking was a viable strategy.  I've always heard that for most guilds who try them, the lords are 50+ person raids.  It looked like this guild was trying it with under 30 people and they got the lord down over halfway before they lost the pets.  Once the pets were dead, the meleers tried to step in, but everyone was dead soon afterward.  If they add some more nukers/charmers and a couple more charmers, they could take out the lord while the meleers all sat on their bums watching.  <br>
<br>
Meleers... your job these days is to pull and get the hell out of the way.  A chanter/cleric are going to get way faster exp on their own, but If the chanter/healer are nice enough to let you leech exp off them, you might want to chip in sometimes by meat shielding when charm breaks.  Then please return to sitting on your bum.  Have a nice day.<br>
