<br>
2) Charm is very uber yes. But, there's no such thing as a free lunch. When that charm breaks, there damn well better be a tank there because the uncharmed haste pet will make mince-meat out of the charming chanter. This is why most of the time these people have druids(it's a mixed druid/enchanter thing with the frogs) keep them snared. Kite+recharm, problem solved.<br>
<br>
3) Pets don't need to taunt, as long as they are the ones in range they will keep aggro.<br>
<br>
4) Keep in mind, chanters have to control group slow, haste, buffs, mez. Pets don't instantly attack, so you have to get pets to attack. You do this by targeting a giant, and hitting /pet attack for charmed mobs.<br>
<br>
5) Charm is not fixed duration; but very random. Nevertheless, it's not especially hard to recharm a mob once it does break.<br>
<br>
6) VI already said they will be nerfing charm in the near future. Unfortunately, they've already nerfed the crap out of affliction items(this means your shammies and chanters got a big nerf to cast times/durations/mana costs of spells like malo, tash, slow, and mez) due to their usual ineptness. Instead of actually fixing the problem, the dev team is especially fond of fumbling around with it like a teenager attempting to unhook his girlfriend's bra for the first time.<br>
<br>
7) Pets don't need to taunt, as long as they are the ones in range they will keep aggro.<br>
<br>
Bottom line: If there are frogs, and charmers, there's no need for melee classes. Just another instance where the dev team didn't understand the game they work on. People have been using charm tactics forever, aka bards+ west wastes in velious era. It doesn't take a genius to figure out that putting stronger charms in game along with perfect charmees like frogs will result in total hosing of risk vs reward. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=azzdaan>azzdaan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/8/03 1:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1874.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Charm leads to a sad day for tanks</span><hr size=1> Guys if you are reffering to and it had to of been. in Pos or any high lvl spot,  Dire charm does not break.  has a reset time of 72mins RL  time, But on the same token they will not replace tanks.    <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=383773&amp;resize=true" target="top">My Magelo Profile</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
